<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-07T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-07T12:00:00-05:00" n="221" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1818</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Russell</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-07T12:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 7, 1916, noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your May 6, 6 a.m., received May 7, 10 a.m. Caperton reports to Navy
                            Department May 6, midnight, that President has canceled request that
                            city be occupied by our forces and has placed his resignation in your
                            hands May 6, 9 p.m.</p>
                        <p>While naturally desirous that bloodshed be avoided, Department believes
                            that manifestly irregular manner of impeachment renders it particularly
                            desirable that President be upheld by every possible and proper means.
                            Previous instructions to you and to naval forces grant authority for
                            such action as you may deem advisable.</p>
                        <p>Additional marines are being sent and Caperton so advised.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>